<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-15T06:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-15T06:29:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/4451</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Archangel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-15T16:00:00+04:31"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            15, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 27, 9.51
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>104. [Your] August 2, 3 [4] p.m. Nine hundred and twenty-nine tons of
                                flax certain, also other cargo about which several telegrams already
                                sent. Port now under absolute Allied control.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_CF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>